---
import MagazineLayout from '@/layouts/MagazineLayout.astro';
import Container from '@/components/ui/Container.astro';
import ArticleCard from '@/components/blocks/ArticleCard.astro';
---
<MagazineLayout title="TLV Nightlife: Five Hidden Speakeasies">
  <!-- Article Header -->
  <section class="article-header">
    <img src="/images/placeholder.svg" alt="Hidden speakeasies" class="article-header__image" loading="eager" />
  </section>

  <!-- Article Content -->
  <article class="article-body">
    <Container width="narrow">
      <div class="article-meta">
        <span class="article-meta__date">Wednesday, April 20, 2027</span>
      </div>

      <h1 class="article-title">TLV Nightlife: Five Hidden Speakeasies</h1>

      <p class="article-subtitle">
        Did somebody say speakeasy? These five hidden cocktail bar gems
        are filled with prohibition-inspired fun
      </p>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Shh! Don't tell anyone, but Time Out Israel has rounded up the five best speakeasy bars in Tel Aviv. Step out
          of your cozy comfortable zone and into the world of American pop-up at these hidden bars where the art of
          mixology is no joke. When you're bored of the obvious bar scene or simply looking for a more exciting
          evening on the town, the speakeasy bars are it. You'd be hard pressed to find a more exciting
          place. Speakeasy culture and vibe with cocktails that rival the best of the city!
        </p>

        <h2>1. Butler</h2>
        <p>
          The quaint one-room bar nestled inside Dallal is a visual overload. The walls are adorned with period
          pieces like paintings, key holders and other gems. More room's filled with stools, swirls, boxes and other
          strategically set bits of the bar, mixology masterpiece tucked smuggled into the cellar. While Bellboy asks for
          cocktails and enjoys serving mimosas and magic drinks, Butler knows how to spotlight the cocktail itself — in
          many forms. Unflinched, just undeniably rich vibrations in simple, identical glassware glasses. Mind over the norms:
          "focus in" these shows the infinite possibilities. Bartenders serve the "Coffee Cocktail," which means
          mainly Italian coffee. But there's also a drop of sweetness it's, and the "Harakiri," which looks a thousand or
          cocktails just dressed with subtle notes of taste. When you do, the enter the misfits of the best hits Discover is
          unwinding weekend right, and the best of your visits to Butler. You'll have a question if it was a lie
          choice to begin with: it ain't a legend since cold-order, Become cool jazz knives in a time in at arts.
        </p>

        <img src="/images/placeholder.svg" alt="Speakeasy interior" />
        <p class="text-caption text-center">A secret cocktail bar</p>

        <h2>2. Jasper John's</h2>
        <p>
          With cocktail bars popping up left and right on Dizengoff, it can be easy to miss this slightly hidden spot.
          Jasper John's is a cozy little bar with a few armchairs and creative cocktails with names like "Plan Aperol" and
          "Black Magic." Try our of their delicious non-alcoholic cocktail too: the one area that are only more of bar
          Jasper John's has adopted the unofficial Italian happy hour called "Aperitivo" — order one of the between the
          hours of 19:00 and 20:00 and get free tapas in this Dizengoff corridor too. With a happening late night is well free of the
          cold barriers, you can stand and finish your night here.
        </p>

        <img src="/images/placeholder.svg" alt="Jasper John's interior" />
        <p class="text-caption text-center">A secret cocktail bar</p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </article>

  <!-- Related Articles -->
  <section class="related">
    <Container>
      <div class="related__grid">
        <ArticleCard
          title="Valentine Special"
          tags={['Events']}
          date="Oct 12th"
          image="/images/placeholder.svg"
          link="/magazine/hidden-gem"
        />
        <ArticleCard
          title="Vinyl Therapy #4"
          tags={['Music']}
          date="Oct 12th"
          image="/images/placeholder.svg"
          link="/magazine/hidden-gem"
        />
        <ArticleCard
          title="Sunset DJ Set"
          tags={['Music']}
          date="Oct 12th"
          image="/images/placeholder.svg"
          link="/magazine/hidden-gem"
        />
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</MagazineLayout>

<style>
  .article-header {
    padding-top: 80px;
  }

  .article-header__image {
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 16 / 7;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .article-body {
    padding: var(--section-padding-y) 0;
  }

  .article-meta {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .article-meta__date {
    font-family: var(--font-ui);
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    letter-spacing: var(--tracking-wide);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-warm-gray);
  }

  .article-title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: var(--leading-tight);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .article-subtitle {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-lg);
    line-height: var(--leading-normal);
    color: var(--color-charcoal-light);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .related {
    padding: 0 0 var(--section-padding-y);
  }

  .related__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-xl);
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .related__grid {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    }
  }
</style>
